32/*
33 * The rdataslab structure allows iteration to occur in both load order
34 * and DNSSEC order. The structure is as follows:
35 *
36 * header (reservelen bytes)
37 * record count (2 bytes)
38 * offset table (4 x record count bytes in load order)
39 * data records
40 * data length (2 bytes)
41 * order (2 bytes)
42 * meta data (1 byte for RRSIG's)
43 * data (data length bytes)
44 *
45 * If DNS_RDATASET_FIXED is defined to be zero (0) the format of a
46 * rdataslab is as follows:
47 *
48 * header (reservelen bytes)
49 * record count (2 bytes)
50 * data records
51 * data length (2 bytes)
52 * meta data (1 byte for RRSIG's)
53 * data (data length bytes)
54 *
55 * Offsets are from the end of the header.
56 *
57 * Load order traversal is performed by walking the offset table to find
58 * the start of the record (DNS_RDATASET_FIXED = 1).
59 *
60 * DNSSEC order traversal is performed by walking the data records.
61 *
62 * The order is stored with record to allow for efficient reconstruction
63 * of the offset table following a merge or subtraction.
64 *
65 * The iterator methods in rbtdb support both load order and DNSSEC order
66 * iteration.
67 *
68 * WARNING:
69 * rbtdb.c directly interacts with the slab's raw structures. If the
70 * structure changes then rbtdb.c also needs to be updated to reflect
71 * the changes. See the areas tagged with "RDATASLAB".
72 */
73
74struct xrdata {
75 dns_rdata_t rdata;
76 unsigned int order;
77};
78
79/*% Note: the "const void *" are just to make qsort happy. */
80static int
81compare_rdata(const void *p1, const void *p2) {
82 const struct xrdata *x1 = p1;
83 const struct xrdata *x2 = p2;
84 return (dns_rdata_compare(&x1->rdata, &x2->rdata));
85}
86
87#if DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
88static void
89fillin_offsets(unsigned char *offsetbase, unsigned int *offsettable,
90 unsigned length)
91{
92 unsigned int i, j;
93 unsigned char *raw;
94
95 for (i = 0, j = 0; i < length; i++) {
96
97 if (offsettable[i] == 0)
98 continue;
99
100 /*
101 * Fill in offset table.
102 */
103 raw = &offsetbase[j*4 + 2];
104 *raw++ = (offsettable[i] & 0xff000000) >> 24;
105 *raw++ = (offsettable[i] & 0xff0000) >> 16;
106 *raw++ = (offsettable[i] & 0xff00) >> 8;
107 *raw = offsettable[i] & 0xff;
108
109 /*
110 * Fill in table index.
111 */
112 raw = offsetbase + offsettable[i] + 2;
113 *raw++ = (j & 0xff00) >> 8;
114 *raw = j++ & 0xff;
115 }
116}
117#endif

119isc_result_t
120dns_rdataslab_fromrdataset(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset, isc_mem_t *mctx,
121 isc_region_t *region, unsigned int reservelen)
122{
123 /*
124 * Use &removed as a sentinal pointer for duplicate
125 * rdata as rdata.data == NULL is valid.
126 */
127 static unsigned char removed;
128 struct xrdata *x;
129 unsigned char *rawbuf;
130#if DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
131 unsigned char *offsetbase;
132#endif
133 unsigned int buflen;
134 isc_result_t result;
135 unsigned int nitems;
136 unsigned int nalloc;
137 unsigned int i;
138#if DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
139 unsigned int *offsettable;
140#endif
141 unsigned int length;
142
143 buflen = reservelen + 2;
144
145 nitems = dns_rdataset_count(rdataset);
146
147 /*
148 * If there are no rdata then we can just need to allocate a header
149 * with zero a record count.
150 */
151 if (nitems == 0) {
152 if (rdataset->type != 0)
153 return (ISC_R_FAILURE);
154 rawbuf = isc_mem_get(mctx, buflen);
155 if (rawbuf == NULL)
156 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
157 region->base = rawbuf;
158 region->length = buflen;
159 rawbuf += reservelen;
160 *rawbuf++ = 0;
161 *rawbuf = 0;
162 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
163 }
164
165 if (nitems > 0xffff)
166 return (ISC_R_NOSPACE);
167
168 /*
169 * Remember the original number of items.
170 */
171 nalloc = nitems;
172 x = isc_mem_get(mctx, nalloc * sizeof(struct xrdata));
173 if (x == NULL)
174 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
175
176 /*
177 * Save all of the rdata members into an array.
178 */
179 result = dns_rdataset_first(rdataset);
180 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS && result != ISC_R_NOMORE)
181 goto free_rdatas;
182 for (i = 0; i < nalloc && result == ISC_R_SUCCESS; i++) {
183 INSIST(result == ISC_R_SUCCESS);
184 dns_rdata_init(&x[i].rdata);
185 dns_rdataset_current(rdataset, &x[i].rdata);
186 INSIST(x[i].rdata.data != &removed);
187#if DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
188 x[i].order = i;
189#endif
190 result = dns_rdataset_next(rdataset);
191 }
192 if (i != nalloc || result != ISC_R_NOMORE) {
193 /*
194 * Somehow we iterated over fewer rdatas than
195 * dns_rdataset_count() said there were or there
196 * were more items than dns_rdataset_count said
197 * there were.
198 */
199 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
200 goto free_rdatas;
201 }
202
203 /*
204 * Put into DNSSEC order.
205 */
206 if (nalloc > 1U)
207 qsort(x, nalloc, sizeof(struct xrdata), compare_rdata);
208
209 /*
210 * Remove duplicates and compute the total storage required.
211 *
212 * If an rdata is not a duplicate, accumulate the storage size
213 * required for the rdata. We do not store the class, type, etc,
214 * just the rdata, so our overhead is 2 bytes for the number of
215 * records, and 8 for each rdata, (length(2), offset(4) and order(2))
216 * and then the rdata itself.
217 */
218 for (i = 1; i < nalloc; i++) {
219 if (compare_rdata(&x[i-1].rdata, &x[i].rdata) == 0) {
220 x[i-1].rdata.data = &removed;
221#if DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
222 /*
223 * Preserve the least order so A, B, A -> A, B
224 * after duplicate removal.
225 */
226 if (x[i-1].order < x[i].order)
227 x[i].order = x[i-1].order;
228#endif
229 nitems--;
230 } else {
231#if DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
232 buflen += (8 + x[i-1].rdata.length);
233#else
234 buflen += (2 + x[i-1].rdata.length);
235#endif
236 /*
237 * Provide space to store the per RR meta data.
238 */
239 if (rdataset->type == dns_rdatatype_rrsig)
240 buflen++;
241 }
242 }
243
244 /*
245 * Don't forget the last item!
246 */
247#if DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
248 buflen += (8 + x[i-1].rdata.length);
249#else
250 buflen += (2 + x[i-1].rdata.length);
251#endif
252 /*
253 * Provide space to store the per RR meta data.
254 */
255 if (rdataset->type == dns_rdatatype_rrsig)
256 buflen++;
257
258 /*
259 * Ensure that singleton types are actually singletons.
260 */
261 if (nitems > 1 && dns_rdatatype_issingleton(rdataset->type)) {
262 /*
263 * We have a singleton type, but there's more than one
264 * RR in the rdataset.
265 */
266 result = DNS_R_SINGLETON;
267 goto free_rdatas;
268 }
269
270 /*
271 * Allocate the memory, set up a buffer, start copying in
272 * data.
273 */
274 rawbuf = isc_mem_get(mctx, buflen);
275 if (rawbuf == NULL) {
276 result = ISC_R_NOMEMORY;
277 goto free_rdatas;
278 }
279
280#if DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
281 /* Allocate temporary offset table. */
282 offsettable = isc_mem_get(mctx, nalloc * sizeof(unsigned int));
283 if (offsettable == NULL) {
284 isc_mem_put(mctx, rawbuf, buflen);
285 result = ISC_R_NOMEMORY;
286 goto free_rdatas;
287 }
288 memset(offsettable, 0, nalloc * sizeof(unsigned int));
289#endif
290
291 region->base = rawbuf;
292 region->length = buflen;
293
294 memset(rawbuf, 0, buflen);
295 rawbuf += reservelen;
296
297#if DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
298 offsetbase = rawbuf;
299#endif
300
301 *rawbuf++ = (nitems & 0xff00) >> 8;
302 *rawbuf++ = (nitems & 0x00ff);
303
304#if DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
305 /* Skip load order table. Filled in later. */
306 rawbuf += nitems * 4;
307#endif
308
309 for (i = 0; i < nalloc; i++) {
310 if (x[i].rdata.data == &removed)
311 continue;
312#if DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
313 offsettable[x[i].order] = rawbuf - offsetbase;
314#endif
315 length = x[i].rdata.length;
316 if (rdataset->type == dns_rdatatype_rrsig)
317 length++;
318 INSIST(length <= 0xffff);
319 *rawbuf++ = (length & 0xff00) >> 8;
320 *rawbuf++ = (length & 0x00ff);
321#if DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
322 rawbuf += 2; /* filled in later */
323#endif
324 /*
325 * Store the per RR meta data.
326 */
327 if (rdataset->type == dns_rdatatype_rrsig) {
328 *rawbuf++ = (x[i].rdata.flags & DNS_RDATA_OFFLINE) ?
329 DNS_RDATASLAB_OFFLINE : 0;
330 }
331 memmove(rawbuf, x[i].rdata.data, x[i].rdata.length);
332 rawbuf += x[i].rdata.length;
333 }
334
335#if DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
336 fillin_offsets(offsetbase, offsettable, nalloc);
337 isc_mem_put(mctx, offsettable, nalloc * sizeof(unsigned int));
338#endif
339
340 result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
341
342 free_rdatas:
343 isc_mem_put(mctx, x, nalloc * sizeof(struct xrdata));
344 return (result);
345}
346
347unsigned int
348dns_rdataslab_size(unsigned char *slab, unsigned int reservelen) {
349 unsigned int count, length;
350 unsigned char *current;
351
352 REQUIRE(slab != NULL);
353
354 current = slab + reservelen;
355 count = *current++ * 256;
356 count += *current++;
357#if DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
358 current += (4 * count);
359#endif
360 while (count > 0) {
361 count--;
362 length = *current++ * 256;
363 length += *current++;
364#if DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
365 current += length + 2;
366#else
367 current += length;
368#endif
369 }
370
371 return ((unsigned int)(current - slab));
372}
373
374unsigned int
375dns_rdataslab_count(unsigned char *slab, unsigned int reservelen) {
376 unsigned int count;
377 unsigned char *current;
378
379 REQUIRE(slab != NULL);
380
381 current = slab + reservelen;
382 count = *current++ * 256;
383 count += *current++;
384 return (count);
385}
386
387/*
388 * Make the dns_rdata_t 'rdata' refer to the slab item
389 * beginning at '*current', which is part of a slab of type
390 * 'type' and class 'rdclass', and advance '*current' to
391 * point to the next item in the slab.
392 */
393static inline void
394rdata_from_slab(unsigned char **current,
395 dns_rdataclass_t rdclass, dns_rdatatype_t type,
396 dns_rdata_t *rdata)
397{
398 unsigned char *tcurrent = *current;
399 isc_region_t region;
400 unsigned int length;
401 bool offline = false;
402
403 length = *tcurrent++ * 256;
404 length += *tcurrent++;
405
406 if (type == dns_rdatatype_rrsig) {
407 if ((*tcurrent & DNS_RDATASLAB_OFFLINE) != 0)
408 offline = true;
409 length--;
410 tcurrent++;
411 }
412 region.length = length;
413#if DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
414 tcurrent += 2;
415#endif
416 region.base = tcurrent;
417 tcurrent += region.length;
418 dns_rdata_fromregion(rdata, rdclass, type, &region);
419 if (offline)
420 rdata->flags |= DNS_RDATA_OFFLINE;
421 *current = tcurrent;
422}
423
424/*
425 * Return true iff 'slab' (slab data of type 'type' and class 'rdclass')
426 * contains an rdata identical to 'rdata'. This does case insensitive
427 * comparisons per DNSSEC.
428 */
429static inline bool
430rdata_in_slab(unsigned char *slab, unsigned int reservelen,
431 dns_rdataclass_t rdclass, dns_rdatatype_t type,
432 dns_rdata_t *rdata)
433{
434 unsigned int count, i;
435 unsigned char *current;
436 dns_rdata_t trdata = DNS_RDATA_INIT;
437 int n;
438
439 current = slab + reservelen;
440 count = *current++ * 256;
441 count += *current++;
442
443#if DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
444 current += (4 * count);
445#endif
446
447 for (i = 0; i < count; i++) {
448 rdata_from_slab(&current, rdclass, type, &trdata);
449
450 n = dns_rdata_compare(&trdata, rdata);
451 if (n == 0)
452 return (true);
453 if (n > 0) /* In DNSSEC order. */
454 break;
455 dns_rdata_reset(&trdata);
456 }
457 return (false);
458}

460isc_result_t
461dns_rdataslab_merge(unsigned char *oslab, unsigned char *nslab,
462 unsigned int reservelen, isc_mem_t *mctx,
463 dns_rdataclass_t rdclass, dns_rdatatype_t type,
464 unsigned int flags, unsigned char **tslabp)
465{
466 unsigned char *ocurrent, *ostart, *ncurrent, *tstart, *tcurrent, *data;
467 unsigned int ocount, ncount, count, olength, tlength, tcount, length;
468 dns_rdata_t ordata = DNS_RDATA_INIT;
469 dns_rdata_t nrdata = DNS_RDATA_INIT;
470 bool added_something = false;
471 unsigned int oadded = 0;
472 unsigned int nadded = 0;
473 unsigned int nncount = 0;
474#if DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
475 unsigned int oncount;
476 unsigned int norder = 0;
477 unsigned int oorder = 0;
478 unsigned char *offsetbase;
479 unsigned int *offsettable;
480#endif
481
482 /*
483 * XXX Need parameter to allow "delete rdatasets in nslab" merge,
484 * or perhaps another merge routine for this purpose.
485 */
486
487 REQUIRE(tslabp != NULL && *tslabp == NULL);
488 REQUIRE(oslab != NULL && nslab != NULL);
489
490 ocurrent = oslab + reservelen;
491 ocount = *ocurrent++ * 256;
492 ocount += *ocurrent++;
493#if DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
494 ocurrent += (4 * ocount);
495#endif
496 ostart = ocurrent;
497 ncurrent = nslab + reservelen;
498 ncount = *ncurrent++ * 256;
499 ncount += *ncurrent++;
500#if DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
501 ncurrent += (4 * ncount);
502#endif
503 INSIST(ocount > 0 && ncount > 0);
504
505#if DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
506 oncount = ncount;
507#endif
508
509 /*
510 * Yes, this is inefficient!
511 */
512
513 /*
514 * Figure out the length of the old slab's data.
515 */
516 olength = 0;
517 for (count = 0; count < ocount; count++) {
518 length = *ocurrent++ * 256;
519 length += *ocurrent++;
520#if DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
521 olength += length + 8;
522 ocurrent += length + 2;
523#else
524 olength += length + 2;
525 ocurrent += length;
526#endif
527 }
528
529 /*
530 * Start figuring out the target length and count.
531 */
532 tlength = reservelen + 2 + olength;
533 tcount = ocount;
534
535 /*
536 * Add in the length of rdata in the new slab that aren't in
537 * the old slab.
538 */
539 do {
540 dns_rdata_init(&nrdata);
541 rdata_from_slab(&ncurrent, rdclass, type, &nrdata);
542 if (!rdata_in_slab(oslab, reservelen, rdclass, type, &nrdata))
543 {
544 /*
545 * This rdata isn't in the old slab.
546 */
547#if DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
548 tlength += nrdata.length + 8;
549#else
550 tlength += nrdata.length + 2;
551#endif
552 if (type == dns_rdatatype_rrsig)
553 tlength++;
554 tcount++;
555 nncount++;
556 added_something = true;
557 }
558 ncount--;
559 } while (ncount > 0);
560 ncount = nncount;
561
562 if (((flags & DNS_RDATASLAB_EXACT) != 0) &&
563 (tcount != ncount + ocount))
564 return (DNS_R_NOTEXACT);
565
566 if (!added_something && (flags & DNS_RDATASLAB_FORCE) == 0)
567 return (DNS_R_UNCHANGED);
568
569 /*
570 * Ensure that singleton types are actually singletons.
571 */
572 if (tcount > 1 && dns_rdatatype_issingleton(type)) {
573 /*
574 * We have a singleton type, but there's more than one
575 * RR in the rdataset.
576 */
577 return (DNS_R_SINGLETON);
578 }
579
580 if (tcount > 0xffff)
581 return (ISC_R_NOSPACE);
582
583 /*
584 * Copy the reserved area from the new slab.
585 */
586 tstart = isc_mem_get(mctx, tlength);
587 if (tstart == NULL)
588 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
589 memmove(tstart, nslab, reservelen);
590 tcurrent = tstart + reservelen;
591#if DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
592 offsetbase = tcurrent;
593#endif
594
595 /*
596 * Write the new count.
597 */
598 *tcurrent++ = (tcount & 0xff00) >> 8;
599 *tcurrent++ = (tcount & 0x00ff);
600
601#if DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
602 /*
603 * Skip offset table.
604 */
605 tcurrent += (tcount * 4);
606
607 offsettable = isc_mem_get(mctx,
608 (ocount + oncount) * sizeof(unsigned int));
609 if (offsettable == NULL) {
610 isc_mem_put(mctx, tstart, tlength);
611 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
612 }
613 memset(offsettable, 0, (ocount + oncount) * sizeof(unsigned int));
614#endif
615
616 /*
617 * Merge the two slabs.
618 */
619 ocurrent = ostart;
620 INSIST(ocount != 0);
621#if DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
622 oorder = ocurrent[2] * 256 + ocurrent[3];
623 INSIST(oorder < ocount);
624#endif
625 rdata_from_slab(&ocurrent, rdclass, type, &ordata);
626
627 ncurrent = nslab + reservelen + 2;
628#if DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
629 ncurrent += (4 * oncount);
630#endif
631
632 if (ncount > 0) {
633 do {
634 dns_rdata_reset(&nrdata);
635#if DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
636 norder = ncurrent[2] * 256 + ncurrent[3];
637
638 INSIST(norder < oncount);
639#endif
640 rdata_from_slab(&ncurrent, rdclass, type, &nrdata);
641 } while (rdata_in_slab(oslab, reservelen, rdclass,
642 type, &nrdata));
643 }
644
645 while (oadded < ocount || nadded < ncount) {
646 bool fromold;
647 if (oadded == ocount)
648 fromold = false;
649 else if (nadded == ncount)
650 fromold = true;
651 else
652 fromold = (dns_rdata_compare(&ordata,
653 &nrdata) < 0);
654 if (fromold) {
655#if DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
656 offsettable[oorder] = tcurrent - offsetbase;
657#endif
658 length = ordata.length;
659 data = ordata.data;
660 if (type == dns_rdatatype_rrsig) {
661 length++;
662 data--;
663 }
664 *tcurrent++ = (length & 0xff00) >> 8;
665 *tcurrent++ = (length & 0x00ff);
666#if DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
667 tcurrent += 2; /* fill in later */
668#endif
669 memmove(tcurrent, data, length);
670 tcurrent += length;
671 oadded++;
672 if (oadded < ocount) {
673 dns_rdata_reset(&ordata);
674#if DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
675 oorder = ocurrent[2] * 256 + ocurrent[3];
676 INSIST(oorder < ocount);
677#endif
678 rdata_from_slab(&ocurrent, rdclass, type,
679 &ordata);
680 }
681 } else {
682#if DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
683 offsettable[ocount + norder] = tcurrent - offsetbase;
684#endif
685 length = nrdata.length;
686 data = nrdata.data;
687 if (type == dns_rdatatype_rrsig) {
688 length++;
689 data--;
690 }
691 *tcurrent++ = (length & 0xff00) >> 8;
692 *tcurrent++ = (length & 0x00ff);
693#if DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
694 tcurrent += 2; /* fill in later */
695#endif
696 memmove(tcurrent, data, length);
697 tcurrent += length;
698 nadded++;
699 if (nadded < ncount) {
700 do {
701 dns_rdata_reset(&nrdata);
702#if DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
703 norder = ncurrent[2] * 256 + ncurrent[3];
704 INSIST(norder < oncount);
705#endif
706 rdata_from_slab(&ncurrent, rdclass,
707 type, &nrdata);
708 } while (rdata_in_slab(oslab, reservelen,
709 rdclass, type,
710 &nrdata));
711 }
712 }
713 }
714
715#if DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
716 fillin_offsets(offsetbase, offsettable, ocount + oncount);
717
718 isc_mem_put(mctx, offsettable,
719 (ocount + oncount) * sizeof(unsigned int));
720#endif
721
722 INSIST(tcurrent == tstart + tlength);
723
724 *tslabp = tstart;
725
726 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
727}

729isc_result_t
730dns_rdataslab_subtract(unsigned char *mslab, unsigned char *sslab,
731 unsigned int reservelen, isc_mem_t *mctx,
732 dns_rdataclass_t rdclass, dns_rdatatype_t type,
733 unsigned int flags, unsigned char **tslabp)
734{
735 unsigned char *mcurrent, *sstart, *scurrent, *tstart, *tcurrent;
736 unsigned int mcount, scount, rcount ,count, tlength, tcount, i;
737 dns_rdata_t srdata = DNS_RDATA_INIT;
738 dns_rdata_t mrdata = DNS_RDATA_INIT;
739#if DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
740 unsigned char *offsetbase;
741 unsigned int *offsettable;
742 unsigned int order;
743#endif
744
745 REQUIRE(tslabp != NULL && *tslabp == NULL);
746 REQUIRE(mslab != NULL && sslab != NULL);
747
748 mcurrent = mslab + reservelen;
749 mcount = *mcurrent++ * 256;
750 mcount += *mcurrent++;
751 scurrent = sslab + reservelen;
752 scount = *scurrent++ * 256;
753 scount += *scurrent++;
754 INSIST(mcount > 0 && scount > 0);
755
756 /*
757 * Yes, this is inefficient!
758 */
759
760 /*
761 * Start figuring out the target length and count.
762 */
763 tlength = reservelen + 2;
764 tcount = 0;
765 rcount = 0;
766
767#if DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
768 mcurrent += 4 * mcount;
769 scurrent += 4 * scount;
770#endif
771 sstart = scurrent;
772
773 /*
774 * Add in the length of rdata in the mslab that aren't in
775 * the sslab.
776 */
777 for (i = 0; i < mcount; i++) {
778 unsigned char *mrdatabegin = mcurrent;
779 rdata_from_slab(&mcurrent, rdclass, type, &mrdata);
780 scurrent = sstart;
781 for (count = 0; count < scount; count++) {
782 dns_rdata_reset(&srdata);
783 rdata_from_slab(&scurrent, rdclass, type, &srdata);
784 if (dns_rdata_compare(&mrdata, &srdata) == 0)
785 break;
786 }
787 if (count == scount) {
788 /*
789 * This rdata isn't in the sslab, and thus isn't
790 * being subtracted.
791 */
792 tlength += (unsigned int)(mcurrent - mrdatabegin);
793 tcount++;
794 } else
795 rcount++;
796 dns_rdata_reset(&mrdata);
797 }
798
799#if DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
800 tlength += (4 * tcount);
801#endif
802
803 /*
804 * Check that all the records originally existed. The numeric
805 * check only works as rdataslabs do not contain duplicates.
806 */
807 if (((flags & DNS_RDATASLAB_EXACT) != 0) && (rcount != scount))
808 return (DNS_R_NOTEXACT);
809
810 /*
811 * Don't continue if the new rdataslab would be empty.
812 */
813 if (tcount == 0)
814 return (DNS_R_NXRRSET);
815
816 /*
817 * If nothing is going to change, we can stop.
818 */
819 if (rcount == 0)
820 return (DNS_R_UNCHANGED);
821
822 /*
823 * Copy the reserved area from the mslab.
824 */
825 tstart = isc_mem_get(mctx, tlength);
826 if (tstart == NULL)
827 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
828 memmove(tstart, mslab, reservelen);
829 tcurrent = tstart + reservelen;
830#if DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
831 offsetbase = tcurrent;
832
833 offsettable = isc_mem_get(mctx, mcount * sizeof(unsigned int));
834 if (offsettable == NULL) {
835 isc_mem_put(mctx, tstart, tlength);
836 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
837 }
838 memset(offsettable, 0, mcount * sizeof(unsigned int));
839#endif
840
841 /*
842 * Write the new count.
843 */
844 *tcurrent++ = (tcount & 0xff00) >> 8;
845 *tcurrent++ = (tcount & 0x00ff);
846
847#if DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
848 tcurrent += (4 * tcount);
849#endif
850
851 /*
852 * Copy the parts of mslab not in sslab.
853 */
854 mcurrent = mslab + reservelen;
855 mcount = *mcurrent++ * 256;
856 mcount += *mcurrent++;
857#if DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
858 mcurrent += (4 * mcount);
859#endif
860 for (i = 0; i < mcount; i++) {
861 unsigned char *mrdatabegin = mcurrent;
862#if DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
863 order = mcurrent[2] * 256 + mcurrent[3];
864 INSIST(order < mcount);
865#endif
866 rdata_from_slab(&mcurrent, rdclass, type, &mrdata);
867 scurrent = sstart;
868 for (count = 0; count < scount; count++) {
869 dns_rdata_reset(&srdata);
870 rdata_from_slab(&scurrent, rdclass, type, &srdata);
871 if (dns_rdata_compare(&mrdata, &srdata) == 0)
872 break;
873 }
874 if (count == scount) {
875 /*
876 * This rdata isn't in the sslab, and thus should be
877 * copied to the tslab.
878 */
879 unsigned int length;
880 length = (unsigned int)(mcurrent - mrdatabegin);
881#if DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
882 offsettable[order] = tcurrent - offsetbase;
883#endif
884 memmove(tcurrent, mrdatabegin, length);
885 tcurrent += length;
886 }
887 dns_rdata_reset(&mrdata);
888 }
889
890#if DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
891 fillin_offsets(offsetbase, offsettable, mcount);
892
893 isc_mem_put(mctx, offsettable, mcount * sizeof(unsigned int));
894#endif
895
896 INSIST(tcurrent == tstart + tlength);
897
898 *tslabp = tstart;
899
900 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
901}
902
903bool
904dns_rdataslab_equal(unsigned char *slab1, unsigned char *slab2,
905 unsigned int reservelen)
906{
907 unsigned char *current1, *current2;
908 unsigned int count1, count2;
909 unsigned int length1, length2;
910
911 current1 = slab1 + reservelen;
912 count1 = *current1++ * 256;
913 count1 += *current1++;
914
915 current2 = slab2 + reservelen;
916 count2 = *current2++ * 256;
917 count2 += *current2++;
918
919 if (count1 != count2)
920 return (false);
921
922#if DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
923 current1 += (4 * count1);
924 current2 += (4 * count2);
925#endif
926
927 while (count1 > 0) {
928 length1 = *current1++ * 256;
929 length1 += *current1++;
930
931 length2 = *current2++ * 256;
932 length2 += *current2++;
933
934#if DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
935 current1 += 2;
936 current2 += 2;
937#endif
938
939 if (length1 != length2 ||
940 memcmp(current1, current2, length1) != 0)
941 return (false);
942
943 current1 += length1;
944 current2 += length1;
945
946 count1--;
947 }
948 return (true);
949}
950
951bool
952dns_rdataslab_equalx(unsigned char *slab1, unsigned char *slab2,
953 unsigned int reservelen, dns_rdataclass_t rdclass,
954 dns_rdatatype_t type)
955{
956 unsigned char *current1, *current2;
957 unsigned int count1, count2;
958 dns_rdata_t rdata1 = DNS_RDATA_INIT;
959 dns_rdata_t rdata2 = DNS_RDATA_INIT;
960
961 current1 = slab1 + reservelen;
962 count1 = *current1++ * 256;
963 count1 += *current1++;
964
965 current2 = slab2 + reservelen;
966 count2 = *current2++ * 256;
967 count2 += *current2++;
968
969 if (count1 != count2)
970 return (false);
971
972#if DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
973 current1 += (4 * count1);
974 current2 += (4 * count2);
975#endif
976
977 while (count1-- > 0) {
978 rdata_from_slab(&current1, rdclass, type, &rdata1);
979 rdata_from_slab(&current2, rdclass, type, &rdata2);
980 if (dns_rdata_compare(&rdata1, &rdata2) != 0)
981 return (false);
982 dns_rdata_reset(&rdata1);
983 dns_rdata_reset(&rdata2);
984 }
985 return (true);
986}
